 {"id":"frankenpandas-fd90.54","title":"test(readme): Display impls for Scalar/Interval/IntervalClosed/Timestamp/PeriodFreq + Timedelta::format","description":"Several types have documented Display impls (some explicitly pandas-parity-aspiring per their doc comments) but no test pins the formatted output. A regression in any Display impl would silently break printf-style usage that consumers rely on.

Documented contracts:
- Scalar: NaN/NaT/None/bool/int/float/utf8/Timedelta(formatted)
- IntervalClosed: 'left' / 'right' / 'both' / 'neither'
- Interval: '(0, 5]' (pandas str() contract per docstring)
- Timestamp: 'Timestamp[<nanos>, <tz>]' / 'NaT'
- PeriodFreq: alias strings
- Timedelta::format(nanos) → string

Plan: assert format!('{}', ...) for representative inputs of each type.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T16:43:54.570990649Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T16:52:40.199236737Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T16:52:40.197167487Z","close_reason":"completed: 6 Display impls pinned","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"frankenpandas-fd90.54","depends_on_id":"frankenpandas-fd90","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-27T16:43:54.570990649Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
